
[1]refugee

   REFUGEE', n.

   1. One who flies to a shelter or place of safety.

   2. One who, in times of persecution or political commotion, flees to a
   foreign country for safety; as the French refugees, who left France
   after the revocation of the edict of Nantz, and settled in Flanders and
   America; the refugees from Hispaniola, in 1792; and the American
   refugees, who left their country at the revolution.
